----- stdout -----
Import transactions from a file using a named import profile

Usage: borrow-checker import [OPTIONS] --profile <NAME> --counterpart <ACCOUNT_ID> <FILE>

Arguments:
  <FILE>
          File to import

Options:
      --json
          Emit machine-readable JSON instead of human-readable output
          
          [env: BC_JSON=]

      --profile <NAME>
          Name of the import profile to use

      --counterpart <ACCOUNT_ID>
          Account ID for the offsetting (counterpart) posting.
          
          CSV and OFX imports produce single-account raw transactions. This account receives the balancing entry for each imported line.

      --db-path <DB_PATH>
          Path to the SQLite database file
          
          [env: BC_DB_PATH=[TEMP_DIR]/test.db]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
----- stderr -----
